{
  "stem": "16214.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when she found out that she actually was Jewish, she saw just that this is the end of her, of her life in Poland, and especially the shame that she was discovered to be a Jew, someone who is such an antisemite, you know.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She decided that she's going to go to Israel with them.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she came to Israel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she didn't want to have anything to do with that family of hers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was very angry at them for-- for looking for her, for discovering where she is, for uncovering who she is, for messing her life up like this.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so she decided that she rather kills herself, you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I came to talk to her [DRINKS] on several occasions.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I told her about my childhood, and about what happened to me, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I tried to just help her as much as I could.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I really don't know at the end what happened to her.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But she was kept in the psychiatric ward for quite some time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So these were not very fond memories, you know, of-- of another horrifying experience of what can happen to children of the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] But at the end, you know, I didn't want to be embarrassed by-- by my parents, you know.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And after several weeks of thinking about it, I-- I did go to the US Consulate in Tel Aviv, and-- and told them, you know, that I am going to go back-- you know, back to my parents to United States.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And little did I know what kind of questions they're going to be asking me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I was interrogated as some kind of a little Commie.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You know, it was really funny.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I remember that very vividly.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
